“Any kind of pathogen threat can evoke disgust, an emotion of disgust in a person, and the more conservative they are, the more likely they get the actual disgust reaction.”⁣
⁣
The intricacy of the human anatomy regarding evolution is nonetheless one of the fascinating aspects of nature. Dr. Randy Thornhill gives us his best insight into the ever-evolving world of animal and human behavior.⁣
⁣
We discuss various topics, including cryptic female choice, the Parasite Stress Theory, attractiveness, and conservatism. Dr. Thornhill takes us through the ties and correlations between these matters in this new episode.⁣
⁣
Watch or listen to it via the link in my bio.⁣
⁣
Recorded 05/10/21.

node.title: Infectious Disease is Humanity’s Biggest Killer

⁣
This conversation is available on YouTube, Apple Podcasts, and Spotify. Click the link in my bio for all relevant links.⁣
⁣
Recorded 04/29/21.

"When we got there, he put on some music, and he said, “The custom is to observe silence.” So I knew I wasn’t supposed to talk. I didn’t know at the time, but we were listening to the chanting of Maria Sabina, the Mazatec shaman. I think it was very moving, and we sat wrapped up in blankets by the fireplace. His daughter, who was a Ph.D. in nursing, sat in the corner as the monitor in case anything went wrong."⁣
⁣
More of this conversation can be watched via my YouTube channel. Click the link in my bio.⁣
⁣
Recorded 05/14/21.

⁣
My podcast with Carl Ruck and @brian_muraresku was released on Monday. It's available on YouTube, Apple Podcasts, and Spotify.⁣
⁣

⁣

I sat down with Carl Ruck and Brian Muraresku to unravel the secrets of ancient Greek culture and religion and how psychedelics have altered the realities of Western culture.⁣
⁣
@Brian_Muraresku shares how and why he was drawn to research the role of psychedelics within Western civilization. Muraresku is also the author of "The Immortality Key: The Secret History of the Religion With No Name".⁣
⁣
Carl Ruck is an American professor who’s known for his work and extensive research on mythology and religion regarding the sacred role of entheogens; a selection of psychoactive plants that are known for inducing altered states of reality or consciousness.⁣
⁣
This episode was recorded on May 14th, 2021.⁣
⁣
The entire conversation is now available on YouTube, Apple Podcasts, and Spotify. Click the link in my bio to watch or listen.

⁣

"When we got there, he put on some music, and he said, “The custom is to observe silence.” So I knew I wasn’t supposed to talk. I didn’t know at the time, but we were listening to the chanting of Maria Sabina, the Mazatec shaman. I think it was very moving, and we sat wrapped up in blankets by the fireplace. His daughter, who was a Ph.D. in nursing, sat in the corner as the monitor in case anything went wrong."⁣
⁣
More of this conversation can be watched via my YouTube channel. Click the link in my bio.⁣
⁣
Recorded 05/14/21.
